com.xilinx.rapidwright.design

Class Cell

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.xilinx.rapidwright.design.Cell
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Cell>

    public class Cell
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Cell>
    A cell corresponds to the leaf cell within the logical netlist and provides a mapping to a physical location BEL on the device.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • connectPins

        public Net connectPins(java.lang.String myPin,
                       Cell otherCell,
                       java.lang.String otherPin)
        Connects a pin on this cell to another pin on another cell. Assumes there exists no net connecting the two and will create a net (both logical and physical) to connect them.
        Parameters:
        myPin - The physical name of the pin on this cell
        otherCell - The other cell to connect
        otherPin - The physical name of the pin on the other cell
        Returns:
        The physical net that gets created or null if it was unable to create the net.
